# Root-level bin/linux-<arch>/ is the PREBUILT bundle layout the flake's
# short-circuit consumes (flake.nix:prebuiltBinDir). It must NEVER be committed:
# a git flake only sees tracked files, so an uncommitted bin/ keeps in-repo
# builds (self-hosting `yolo -- bash`) compiling from source. A committed bin/
# would silently force every source build into stale prebuilt binaries — the
# exact source drift this design eliminates. Only shipped/baked path: bundles
# carry bin/, never the repo.
/bin/
# Stray root-level Go build artifacts (a bare `go build ./cmd/<x>` drops the
# binary here). The real build channel is dist-go/; these should never be
# tracked (a stale root yolo-parity was committed once — see the audit).
/goprobe
/yolo
/yolo-parity
/yolo-broker-relay
/yolo-host-processes
/yolo-ps
/yolo-cgd
/yolo-journald
/yolo-jail-supervisor
/yolo-oauth-terminator
